#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1220
#, no-c-format
msgid "Managing &slema; updates and snapshots"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1222
#, no-c-format
msgid "Snapshots and updates management only for system administrators"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1223
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only users with the <guimenu>Server administrator</guimenu> role can update "
"the system or perform a rollback to another snapshot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1228
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Cockpit enables you to update your &slema; instance or perform a rollback "
"from the <literal>Software Updates</literal> menu."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1233
#, no-c-format
msgid "Software Updates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: textobject
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1241
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Software Updates view</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1246
#, no-c-format
msgid "Managing updates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1247
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <guimenu>Check for Updates</guimenu> to get a list of new package "
"updates and patches available for your system. You can view each package "
"update or patch information by clicking the blue icon next to the package "
"update/patch. It is recommended to install the patches marked as important "
"as soon as possible."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1254
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To apply the updates and patches, click <guimenu>Update and Reboot</"
"guimenu> . The equivalent of the <command>transactional-update up</command> "
"command is called and a new snapshot of your system is created. After the "
"update completes successfully, your system will be rebooted and the new "
"snapshot set as default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1261
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can postpone the reboot of your system after the update process by "
"selecting <guimenu>Update without Reboot</guimenu> from the three-dot menu. "
"Bear in mind that you need to reboot the system to activate the snapshot "
"with updates. If you perform further changes without rebooting the system "
"beforehand, a new snapshot will be created from the same point as the "
"snapshots with updates. Therefore, the new snapshot will not include the "
"updates."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1270
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also update &slema; using CLI. For details, refer to <xref linkend="
"\"sec-command-list\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1276
#, no-c-format
msgid "Performing rollbacks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1277
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In <literal>Snapshots &amp; Updates</literal> you can perform a rollback to "
"one of older snapshots by clicking <guimenu>Rollback and Reboot</guimenu> , "
"or <guimenu>Rollback without Reboot</guimenu> in three-dot menu."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1283
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After rebooting the system, the snapshot you rolled back to will be set as "
"active. Do not make any changes (install updates, packages, etc.) before "
"rebooting your system, as the snapshot you rolled back to is not active. Any "
"changes performed before you reboot your system will start from the "
"currently active snapshot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For a system rollback procedure performed using CLI, refer to <xref linkend="
"\"sec-rollback-procedure\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1298
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>toolbox</literal> for &slema; debugging"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&slema; uses the <command>transactional-update</command> command to apply "
"changes to the system, but the changes are applied only after reboot. That "
"solution has several benefits, but it also has some disadvantages. If you "
"need to debug your system and install a new tool, the tool will be available "
"only after reboot. Therefore you are not able to debug the current file "
"system. For this reason a utility called <literal>toolbox</literal> has been "
"developed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1308
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>toolbox</literal> is a small script that pulls a container image "
"and runs a privileged container based on that image. In the toolbox "
"container you can install any tool you want with <command>zypper</command> "
"and then use the tool without rebooting your system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1314
#, no-c-format
msgid "To start the <literal>toolbox</literal> container, run the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1317
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;/usr/bin/toolbox"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1318
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the script completes successfully, you will see the <literal>toolbox</"
"literal> container prompt."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1323
#, no-c-format
msgid "Obtaining the <literal>toolbox</literal> image"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also use Podman or Cockpit to pull the <literal>toolbox</literal> "
"image and start a container based on that image."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1331
#, no-c-format
msgid "Monitoring performance"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For performance monitoring purposes, &slema; provides a container image that "
"enables you to run the Performance Co-Pilot (PCP) analysis toolkit in a "
"container. The toolkit comprises tools for gathering and processing "
"performance information collected either in real time or from PCP archive "
"logs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1338
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The performance data are collected by <emphasis>performance metrics domain "
"agents</emphasis> and passed to the <emphasis>pmcd</emphasis> daemon. The "
"daemon coordinates the gathering and exporting of performance statistics in "
"response to requests from the PCP monitoring tools. <command>pmlogger</"
"command> is then used to log the metrics. For details, refer to the <link "
"xlink:href=\"https://pcp.readthedocs.io/en/latest/UAG/IntroductionToPcp.html#"
"\">PCP documentation</link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1349
#, no-c-format
msgid "Getting the PCP container image"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1350
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The PCP container image is based on the <emphasis>BCI-Init</emphasis> "
"container that utilizes &systemd; used to manage the PCP services."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can pull the container image using podman or from the Cockpit web "
"management console. To pull the image by using podman, run the following "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1359
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;podman pull registry.suse.com/suse/pcp:latest"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To get the container image using Cockpit, go to <guimenu>Podman containers</"
"guimenu> , click <guimenu>Get new image</guimenu> , and search for "
"<emphasis>pcp</emphasis> . Then select the image from the <literal>registry."
"suse.com</literal> for SLE 15 SP3 and download it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1368
#, no-c-format
msgid "Running the PCP container"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1369
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following command shows minimal options that you need to use to run a "
"PCP container:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1373
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;podman run -d  \\\n"
"  --systemd always \\\n"
"  -p <replaceable>HOST_IP:HOST_PORT:CONTAINER_PORT</replaceable> \\\n"
"  -v <replaceable>HOST_DIR</replaceable>:/var/log/pcp/pmlogger \\\n"
"  <replaceable>PCP_CONTAINER_IMAGE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1378
#, no-c-format
msgid "where the options have the following meaning:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1383
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-d</option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1385
#, no-c-format
msgid "The container will run in a detached mode without tty."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1391
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>--systemd always</option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1393
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Runs the container in the &systemd; mode. All services needed to run in the "
"PCP container will be started automatically by &systemd; in the container."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1401
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>--privileged</option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1403
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The container runs with extended privileges. Use this option if your system "
"has SELinux enabled, otherwise the collected metrics will be incomplete."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1411
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>-v <replaceable>HOST_DIR</replaceable>:/var/log/pcp/pmlogger</option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1413
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Creates a bind mount so that <command>pmlogger</command> archives are "
"written to the <replaceable>HOST_DIR</replaceable> on the host. By default, "
"<command>pmlogger</command> stores the collected metrics in <filename>/var/"
"log/pcp/pmlogger</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1421
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>PCP_CONTAINER_IMAGE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1423
#, no-c-format
msgid "Is the downloaded PCP container image."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1429
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Other useful options of the <command>podman run</command> command follow:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1433
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1435
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>-p <replaceable>HOST_IP:HOST_PORT:CONTAINER_PORT</replaceable></"
"option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1437
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Publishes ports of the container by mapping a container port onto a host "
"port. If you do not specify <replaceable>HOST_IP</replaceable> , the ports "
"will be mapped on the local host. If you omit the <replaceable>HOST_PORT</"
"replaceable> value, a random port number will be used. By default, the "
"<command>pmcd</command> daemon listens and exposes the PMAPI to receive "
"metrics on the port <emphasis>44321</emphasis> , so it is recommended to map "
"this port on the same port number on the host. The <command>pmproxy</"
"command> daemon listens on and exposes the REST PMWEBAPI to access metrics "
"on the <emphasis>44322</emphasis> port by default, so it is recommended to "
"map this port on the same host port number."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1453
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>--net host</option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1455
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The container uses the host's network. Use this option if you want to "
"collect metrics from the host's network interfaces."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1462
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-e</option>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1464
#, no-c-format
msgid "The option enables you to set the following environment variables:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1470
#, no-c-format
msgid "PCP_SERVICES"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1472
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Is a comma-separated list of services to start by &systemd; in the container."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1476
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Default services are: <literal>pmcd</literal> , <literal>pmie</literal> , "
"<literal>pmlogger</literal> , <literal>pmproxy</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1481
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use this variable, if you want to run a container with a list of "
"services that is different from the default one, for example, only with "
"<literal>pmlogger</literal> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1486
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;podman run -d \\\n"
"  --name pmlogger \\\n"
"  --systemd always \\\n"
"  -e PCP_SERVICES=pmlogger  \\\n"
"  -v pcp-archives:/var/log/pcp/pmlogger  \\\n"
"  registry.suse.com/suse/pcp:latest"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1495
#, no-c-format
msgid "HOST_MOUNT"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1497
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Is a path inside the container to the bind mount of the host's root file "
"system. The default value is not set."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1503
#, no-c-format
msgid "REDIS_SERVERS"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1505
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies a connection to a Redis server. In a non-clustered setup, provide "
"a comma-separated list of hosts specs. In a clustered setup, provide any "
"individual cluster host, other hosts in the cluster are discovered "
"automatically. The default value is: <literal>localhost:6379</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1515
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you need to use different configuration then provided by the environment "
"variables, proceed as described in <xref linkend=\"sec-pcp-services-"
"configuration\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1525
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring PCP services"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1526
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All services that run inside the PCP container have a default configuration "
"that might not suit your needs. If you need a custom configuration that "
"cannot be covered by the environment variables described above, create "
"configuration files for the PCP services and pass them to the PCP using a "
"bind mount as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1533
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;podman run -d \\\n"
"  --name <replaceable>CONTAINER_NAME</replaceable> \\\n"
"  --systemd always \\\n"
"  -v $<replaceable>HOST_CONFIG</replaceable>:"
"<replaceable>CONTAINER_CONFIG_PATH</replaceable>:z \\\n"
"  -v <replaceable>HOST_LOGS_PATH</replaceable>:/var/log/pcp/pmlogger  \\\n"
"  registry.suse.com/suse/pcp:latest"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1539
#, no-c-format
msgid "Where:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1544
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>CONTAINER_NAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1546
#, no-c-format
msgid "Is an optional container name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1552
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>HOST_CONFIG</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1554
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Is an absolute path to the config you created on the host machine. You can "
"choose any file name you want."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1561
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>CONTAINER_CONFIG_PATH</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1563
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Is an absolute path to a particular configuration file inside the container. "
"Each available configuration file is described in the corresponding sections "
"further."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1571
#, no-c-format
msgid "<replaceable>HOST_LOGS_PATH</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1573
#, no-c-format
msgid "Is a directory that should be bind mount to the container logs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1579
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, a container called <literal>pcp</literal> , with the "
"configuration file <filename>pmcd</filename> on the host machine and the "
"<filename>pcp-archives</filename> directory for logs on the host machine, is "
"run by the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1585
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;podman run -d \\\n"
"  --name pcp  \\\n"
"  --systemd always \\\n"
"  -v $(pwd)/pcp-archives:/var/log/pcp/pmlogger \\\n"
"  -v $(pwd)/pmcd:/etc/sysconfig/pmcd \\\n"
"registry.suse.com/suse/pcp:latest"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1592
#, no-c-format
msgid "Custom <command>pmcd</command> daemon configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1593
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>pmcd</command> daemon configuration is stored in the <filename>/"
"etc/sysconfig/pmcd</filename> file. The file stores environment variables "
"that modify the behavior of the <command>pmcd</command> daemon."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1600
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <filename>/etc/sysconfig/pmcd</filename> file"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can add the following variables to the file to configure the "
"<command>pmcd</command> daemon:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1607
#, no-c-format
msgid "PMCD_LOCAL"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1609
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines whether the remote host can connect to the <command>pmcd</command> "
"daemon. If set to <emphasis>0</emphasis> , remote connections to the daemon "
"are allowed. If set to <emphasis>1</emphasis> , the daemon listens only on "
"the local host. The default value is <emphasis>0</emphasis> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1619
#, no-c-format
msgid "PMCD_MAXPENDING"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1621
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines the maximum count of pending connections to the agent. The default "
"value is 5."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1628
#, no-c-format
msgid "PMCD_ROOT_AGENT"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1630
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the <literal>pmdaroot</literal> is enabled (the value is set to "
"<emphasis>1</emphasis> ), adding a new PDMA does not trigger restarting of "
"other PMDAs. If <literal>pmdaroot</literal> is not enabled, <command>pmcd</"
"command> will require to restart all PMDAs when a new PMDA is added. The "
"default value is <emphasis>1</emphasis> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1640
#, no-c-format
msgid "PMCD_RESTART_AGENTS"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1642
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If set to <emphasis>1</emphasis> , the <command>pmcd</command> daemon tries "
"to restart any exited PMDA. Enable this option only if you have enabled "
"<literal>pmdaroot</literal> , as <command>pmcd</command> itself does not "
"have privileges to restart PMDA."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1651
#, no-c-format
msgid "PMCD_WAIT_TIMEOUT"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1653
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines the maximum time in seconds, <command>pmcd</command> can wait to "
"accept a connection. After this time, the connection is reported as failed. "
"The default value is <emphasis>60</emphasis> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1661
#, no-c-format
