#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1711
#, no-c-format
msgid "Custom <command>pmlogger</command> configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1712
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The custom configuration for the <command>pmlogger</command> is stored in "
"the following configuration files:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1718
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/etc/sysconfig/pmlogger</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1723
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>/etc/pcp/pmlogger/control.d/local</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1733
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <filename>/etc/sysconfig/pmlogger</filename> file"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1734
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use the following attributes to configure the <command>pmlogger</"
"command> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1740
#, no-c-format
msgid "PMLOGGER_LOCAL"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1742
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines whether <command>pmlogger</command> allows connections from remote "
"hosts. If set to <emphasis>1</emphasis> , <command>pmlogger</command> allows "
"connections from local host only."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1750
#, no-c-format
msgid "PMLOGGER_MAXPENDING"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1752
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines the maximum count of pending connections. The default value is 5."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1759
#, no-c-format
msgid "PMLOGGER_INTERVAL"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1761
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines the default sampling interval <command>pmlogger</command> uses. The "
"default value is <emphasis>60&nbsp;s</emphasis> . Keep in mind that this "
"value can be overridden by the <command>pmlogger</command> command line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1770
#, no-c-format
msgid "PMLOGGER_CHECK_SKIP_LOGCONF"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1772
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Setting this option to <emphasis>yes</emphasis> disables the regeneration "
"and checking of the <command>pmlogger</command> configuration if the "
"configuration <command>pmlogger</command> comes from <command>pmlogconf</"
"command> . The default behavior is to regenerate configuration files and "
"check for changes every time <command>pmlogger</command> is started."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1783
#, no-c-format
msgid "An example follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1786
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"PMLOGGER_LOCAL=1\n"
"PMLOGGER_MAXPENDING=5\n"
"PMLOGGER_INTERVAL=10\n"
"PMLOGGER_CHECK_SKIP_LOGCONF=yes\n"
"     "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1794
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <filename>/etc/pcp/pmlogger/control.d/local</filename> file"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1795
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The file <filename>/etc/pcp/pmlogger/control.d/local</filename> stores "
"specifications of the host, which metrics should be logged, the logging "
"frequency (default is 24 hours), and <command>pmlogger</command> options. "
"For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1801
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"# === VARIABLE ASSIGNMENTS ===\n"
"#\n"
"# DO NOT REMOVE OR EDIT THE FOLLOWING LINE\n"
"$version=1.1\n"
"\n"
"# Uncomment one of the lines below to enable/disable compression behaviour\n"
"# that is different to the pmlogger_daily default.\n"
"# Value is days before compressing archives, 0 is immediate compression,\n"
"# \"never\" or \"forever\" suppresses compression.\n"
"#\n"
"#$PCP_COMPRESSAFTER=0 \n"
"#$PCP_COMPRESSAFTER=3\n"
"#$PCP_COMPRESSAFTER=never\n"
"    \n"
"# === LOGGER CONTROL SPECIFICATIONS ===\n"
"#   \n"
"#Host           P?  S?  directory                       args\n"
"\n"
"# local primary logger\n"
"LOCALHOSTNAME   y   n   PCP_ARCHIVE_DIR/LOCALHOSTNAME   -r -T24h10m -c "
"config.default -v 100Mb\n"
"     "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1824
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defaults point to local host"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1825
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you run the <command>pmlogger</command> in a container on a different "
"machine than the one that runs the <command>pmcd</command> (a client), "
"change the following line to point to the client:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1830
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# local primary logger\n"
"<replaceable>CLIENT_HOSTNAME</replaceable>   y   n   PCP_ARCHIVE_DIR/"
"<replaceable>CLIENT_HOSTNAME</replaceable>   -r -T24h10m -c config.default -"
"v 100Mb"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1832
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, for the <literal>slemicro_1</literal> host name, the line "
"should look as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1836
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# local primary logger\n"
"slemicro_1   y   n   PCP_ARCHIVE_DIR/slemicro_1   -r -T24h10m -c config."
"default -v 100Mb"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1853
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starting the PCP container automatically on boot"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1854
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After you run the PCP container, you can configure &systemd; to start the "
"container on boot. To do so, follow the procedure below:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1860
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create a unit file for the container by using the <command>podman generate "
"systemd</command> command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1864
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;podman generate systemd --name <replaceable>CONTAINER_NAME</"
"replaceable> &gt; /etc/systemd/system/container-<replaceable>CONTAINER_NAME</"
"replaceable>.service"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1865
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"where <replaceable>CONTAINER_NAME</replaceable> is the name of the PCP "
"container you used when running the container from the container image."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1871
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable the service in &systemd;:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1874
#, no-c-format
