#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1879
#, no-c-format
msgid "Metrics management"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1881
#, no-c-format
msgid "Listing available performance metrics"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1882
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From within the container, you can use the command <command>pminfo</command> "
"to list metrics. For example, to list all available performance metrics, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1886
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;pminfo"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1887
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can list a group of related metrics by specifying the metrics prefix:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1890
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;pminfo <replaceable>METRIC_PREFIX</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1891
#, no-c-format
msgid "For example, to list all metrics related to kernel, use:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1894
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;pminfo disk\n"
"\n"
"disk.dev.r_await\n"
"disk.dm.await\n"
"disk.dm.r_await\n"
"disk.md.await\n"
"disk.md.r_await\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1903
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also specify additional strings to narrow down the list of metrics, "
"for example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1907
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;piminfo disk.dev\n"
"\n"
"disk.dev.read\n"
"disk.dev.write\n"
"disk.dev.total\n"
"disk.dev.blkread\n"
"disk.dev.blkwrite\n"
"disk.dev.blktotal\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1917
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To get online help text of a particular metric, use the <option>-t</option> "
"option followed by the metric, for example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1921
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;pminfo -t kernel.cpu.util.user\n"
"\n"
"kernel.cpu.util.user [percentage of user time across all CPUs, including "
"guest CPU time]\n"
"      "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1925
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To display a description text of a particular metric, use the <option>-T</"
"option> option followed by the metric, for example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1929
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;pminfo -T kernel.cpu.util.user\n"
"\n"
"Help:\n"
"percentage of user time across all CPUs, including guest CPU time\n"
"      "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1936
#, no-c-format
msgid "Checking local metrics"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1937
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After you start the PCP container, you can verify that metrics are being "
"recorded properly by running the following command inside the container:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1941
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;pcp\n"
"\n"
"Performance Co-Pilot configuration on localhost:\n"
"\n"
" platform: Linux localhost 5.3.18-150300.59.68-default #1 SMP Wed May 4 "
"11:29:09 UTC 2022 (ea30951) x86_64\n"
" hardware: 1 cpu, 1 disk, 1 node, 1726MB RAM\n"
" timezone: UTC\n"
" services: pmcd pmproxy\n"
"     pmcd: Version 5.2.2-1, 9 agents, 4 clients\n"
"     pmda: root pmcd proc pmproxy xfs linux mmv kvm jbd2\n"
" pmlogger: primary logger: /var/log/pcp/pmlogger/localhost/20220607.09.24\n"
"     pmie: primary engine: /var/log/pcp/pmie/localhost/pmie.log\n"
"      "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1954
#, no-c-format
msgid "Now check if the logs are written to a proper destination:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1957
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;ls <replaceable>PATH_TO_PMLOGGER_LOGS</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1958
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"where <replaceable>PATH_TO_PMLOGGER_LOGS</replaceable> should be <filename>/"
"var/log/pcp/pmlogger/localhost/</filename> in this case."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1964
#, no-c-format
msgid "Recording metrics from remote systems"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1965
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can deploy collector containers that collect metrics from different "
"remote systems than the ones where the <command>pmlogger</command> "
"containers are running. Each remote collector system needs the "
"<command>pmcd</command> daemon and a set of <emphasis>pmda</emphasis> . To "
"deploy several collectors with a centralized monitoring system, proceed as "
"follows."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1974
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On each system you want to collect metrics from (clients), run a container "
"with the <command>pmcd</command> daemon:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1978
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;podman run -d \\\n"
"    --name pcp-pmcd \\\n"
"    --privileged \\\n"
"    --net host \\\n"
"    --systemd always \\\n"
"    -e PCP_SERVICES=pmcd \\\n"
"    -e HOST_MOUNT=/host \\\n"
"    -v /:/host:ro,rslave \\\n"
"    registry.suse.com/suse/pcp:latest"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1989
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the monitoring system, create a <command>pmlogger</command> configuration "
"file for each client <filename>control.<replaceable>CLIENT</replaceable></"
"filename> with the following content:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:1995
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"$version=1.1\n"
" \n"
"<replaceable>CLIENT_HOSTNAME</replaceable> n n PCP_ARCHIVE_DIR/"
"<replaceable>CLIENT</replaceable> -N -r -T24h10m -c config.default -v 100Mb\n"
"          "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2000
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Keep in mind that the <replaceable>CLIENT_HOSTNAME</replaceable> must be "
"resolvable in DNS. You can use IP addresses or fully qualified domain names "
"(FQDN) instead."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2007
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the monitoring system, create a directory for each client to store the "
"recorded logs:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2011
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;mkdir /root/pcp-archives/<replaceable>CLIENT</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2012
#, no-c-format
msgid "For example, for <literal>slemicro_1</literal> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2015
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.root;mkdir /root/pcp-archives/slemicro_1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2018
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the monitoring system, run a container with <command>pmlogger</command> "
"for each client:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2022
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;podman run -d \\\n"
"    --name pcp-pmlogger-<replaceable>CLIENT</replaceable> \\\n"
"    --systemd always \\\n"
"    -e PCP_SERVICES=pmlogger \\\n"
"    -v /root/pcp-archives/<replaceable>CLIENT</replaceable>:/var/log/pcp/"
"pmlogger:z \\\n"
"    -v $(pwd)/control.<replaceable>CLIENT</replaceable>:/etc/pcp/pmlogger/"
"control.d/local:z \\\n"
"    registry.suse.com/suse/pcp:latest\n"
"          "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2030
#, no-c-format
msgid "For example, for a client called <literal>slemicro_1</literal> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2033
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;podman run -d \\\n"
"    --name pcp-pmlogger-slemicro_1 \\\n"
"    --systemd always \\\n"
"    -e PCP_SERVICES=pmlogger \\\n"
"    -v /root/pcp-archives:/var/log/pcp/pmlogger:z \\\n"
"    -v $(pwd)/control.slemicro_1:/etc/pcp/pmlogger/control.d/local:z \\\n"
"    registry.suse.com/suse/pcp:latest\n"
"          "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2042
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The second bind mount points to the configuration file created in <xref "
"linkend=\"pmlogger-config\"/> and replaces the default <command>pmlogger</"
"command> configuration. If you do not create this bind mount, "
"<command>pmlogger</command> uses the default <filename>/etc/pcp/pmlogger/"
"control.d/local</filename> file and logging from clients fails as the "
"default configuration points to a local host. For details about the "
"configuration file, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-control-local\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2055
#, no-c-format
msgid "To check if the logs collection is working properly, run:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2058
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.root;ls -l pcp-archives/<replaceable>CLIENT</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>CLIENT</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: art_admin_slemicro.xml:2059
#, no-c-format
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
